This is a collection of some of my Netbox scripts that I use in my job. They all require pynetbox to function, so make sure you have that installed.

assign-ips: This was used when importing all of my devices to Netbox - it's not so easy to import devices with their IP address assigned. So, I imported all IP addresses with the device's serial number as the description of the IP. This script scans all the IPs and descriptions and associates the IP with the corresponding device.

settoinventory: When I'm bringing in a bunch of inventory of switches, I use a bluetooth barcode scanner and this script allows me to just have the terminal open with this script running and scan all the devices without touching my pc. It's a weird little use case just for me, but very handy.